The paper deals with multi-label music style classification, which involves analyzing and categorizing music based on its style. This task involves several sub-fields of computer science, including information retrieval (IR), machine learning (LG), computational linguistics (CL), and multimedia (MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework that integrates external knowledge to capture complete style correlations, which could fall under the sub-category of software development (SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, and cs.MM, in that order.
